comments.content:
@Jens: I must add that I like my home brew Avant Garde more. Not complaining, just saying... :) Appreciated though, sure saved me a lot of work.

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20140713130622im_/http:/typophile.com/files/savant_4880.png)

It's good to have these issues sorted out. It's not the first time I've thought of modifying typefaces for customers. I think the point is that if the license state that you can alter the font for personal use, you can also hire someone to do the modifications. See [http://www.adobe.com/type/topics/licenseqa.html#q25](http://web.archive.org/web/20140713130622/http:/www.adobe.com/type/topics/licenseqa.html#q25) for example. Hope I've got the meaning of "personal use" right in this context.
